<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-08-23T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-08-23T08:00:00-05:00" n="439" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d439">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">881.113/32: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Diplomatic Agent and Consul General at
                                    Tangier</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Blake</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tangier</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-08-23T13:00:00+00:00">August 23, 1936—1
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received August 24—10:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>21. My telegram No. 20, August 20, 5 p.m. Regarding dahir August 17.
                                Representatives of powers in Tangier expecting French to press for
                                adoption in Tangier Zone of similar prohibitions. Doubtful whether
                                Committee of Control would give approval. If French zone dahir is
                                intended to be bona fide neutrality measure it should in my opinion
                                embrace all Spain and not be confined merely as it does to territory
                                held by one party in the conflict.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Blake</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>